// useSnippet
// Provides access to the snippet list and operations, including an API-backed update that persists to the server.

Read/select/add/remove operations delegate directly to the session store.
updateSnippet is enhanced: it calls the API first, then updates the store on success.

FUNCTION useSnippet() -> UseSnippetReturn                                       EXPORT
  CALLS: useSessionStore (sessionStore), api (api)
  Reads snippets, selectedSnippetId, and store actions using shallow comparison.
  Derives selectedSnippet by finding the snippet matching selectedSnippetId.
  Exposes: snippets, selectedSnippetId, selectedSnippet, addSnippet, updateSnippet, removeSnippet,
  selectSnippet, setSnippets, getSnippetById, hasSnippet.

---

FUNCTION updateSnippet(id, content)
  CALLS: api (api)
  Calls the API to persist the updated snippet content. On success, updates the store with the new
  content and a fresh lastModified timestamp. On failure, logs and rethrows the error.

---

FUNCTION getSnippetById(id) -> Snippet | undefined
  Finds and returns the snippet with the given id from the current list.

---

FUNCTION hasSnippet(id) -> boolean
  Returns true if a snippet with the given id exists in the current list.
